            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> United Airlines Refund Policy</h3>

            <p class="text-justify">United has worked hard to make its policies as customer-friendly as possible. The United Airlines Refund Policy ensures that customers receive their money back. All you need to do is be aware of the policies so that you'll be able to collect the reimbursement you've been waiting for in a short amount of time. If United cancels your flight, you will be given a total refund of your money. To do so, make sure you have filled out the refund form completely. </p>

            <p class="text-justify">Assume you changed your flight within the first twenty-four hours of booking. You won't be charged a change fee if you do this and your money will be returned to you directly to your bank account. Within seven to twenty business days, you should receive your reimbursement. If you paid with cash, you'll get your refund in 20 business days; if you paid with a credit card, you'll get your refund in 20 business days. Then, within seven business days, you'll receive your rebate. If you've changed flights, double-check that the new flight has the same designation as the previous one. You won't be able to change your flight until that time has passed. You can claim your refund by filling out the form or contacting customer service. But make sure you do it within 48 hours of modifying. </p>

